**Overall meaning:**

"When both soles of the feet are placed on top of the thighs, this becomes the lotus posture (padmasana), which removes all diseases and poisons."

**Explanation:**

This verse describes the "padmasana" posture, emphasizing its benefits for physical and mental well-being. The verse explains how the posture is achieved by placing the feet on the thighs, creating a lotus-like shape.  The verse then highlights the therapeutic benefits of this posture, claiming that it removes all diseases and poisons.  

The "padmasana" posture is considered highly beneficial because it promotes flexibility, balance, and inner peace.  It is a powerful posture for meditation and spiritual practice, as it allows the practitioner to focus their attention inward without distractions. 


